text: Basically, because Aaron Forsythe says it will be so.
Anyone else fine w Sol Ring? I mean it’s obviously super strong but unless you’re playing cedh it never seems busted to me.
I'm always fine with it. EDH is about doing silly things and it's equitable and available to all.
Plus everyone has access to it

I’ve seen a not insignificant amount of Sol Ring hate from people running Vault and Crypt too. A lot of that is “if it’s legal then run it” but I think there’s also a section of the haters that want it gone so the can run their ow busted rocks, Grim Monolith etc that the plebes can’t afford.
Sol ring isn’t the busted part, command tower into sol ring is the busted part
That’s why you auto win at my playgroup
I just think if your issue is really the power you’d have issue w Vault and Crypt too, and the fact that the anti Sol Ring people rarely do makes me question the integrity of their objections
I think my biggest problem with Sol Ring is that excluding it from a decklist is wrong 99% of the time.
That would probably be true of Vault, Crypt, and Grim Monolith were they two dollar cards
You’re not wrong but it’s not just Sol Ring where that’s true
Cavern of Souls is in more decks than Command Tower even if just to name your commander if it’s a buck
I think if you ban Sol Ring you have to hit all the busted rocks
Yup, and if that were the case I’d likely hold the same opinion.
Not just the ones poors can play
i use to think we should ban sol ring, but now i think it just adds variance to games and makes them a bit more interesting
i dont think my playgroup ever cares about games being fair or whatever
not once have i ever heard "ah that game was bullshit because bobby got a t1 sol ring"
if anything it's like "oh man do you remember that time bobby got a 10 mana on t2 and did some bonkers shit? that was hilarious"
Or “remember that time Bobby got 10 mana on t2, was hellbent and got focused out?”
I'm not necessarily not in favor of banning all the fast rocks *but* Sol Ring.
Fast rocks being monolith, Crypt and the like.
But not signets or talismans
I agree w the variance part too, especially now that partial Paris being gone makes it harder to sculpt the perfect opener
My problem with stopping that is it also enhances green's ability to ramp faster than everyone to an even greater degree.
That's what Keldon Firebombers, Bend or Break and Ward of Bones are for, Henry.
Signets, Talismans and even Monolith are way less busted without the t1 Vault or Crypt or Sol Ring
Which pushes people to make more decks with green to compensate. It hoses most mono-decks.
IMO people over shit themselves about green ramp too
Nope - it's part of the color, but without access to fast ramp, the other colors can't keep up at all
None of it is t1 besides fragile don’t kid
Dorks
I think tables can self regulate that w focus
But then do you want to waste your removal on dorks to keep green in check?
There's stuff like Night of Soul's Betrayal that takes care of dorks easy peasy
Though, I guess you do have to wait until T4 to drop it.
and by that time they're on turn 8
Plus think of all the sweet sweet tears from Kozolik players being deprived of their rocks. Like fine wine.
Removing the player also removes the dorks
I think you just have to live with dorks. Force the players to chump with them, or they got caught as collateral by a Wrath.
More people should run Pestilence anyway
I’ve seen plenty of decks over ramp too
Sure, but that's an individual issue vs. something systemic.
Toxic Deluge is a thing. Are there other wide-reaching, low CMC effects that can deal with multiple dorks?
[[Smoke]] is a good one.

I think philosophically it becomes, do you want EDH to be a format of deep and calculated plays and only use the most efficient pieces, because removing the fast rocks pushes the format in that direction. That isn't a good or bad thing, but if your format is designed to be 'battlecruiser magic' then it's a problem.
I'm not sure I see that analysis
Because using only th emost efficient pieces means running the broken rocks, something most people can't afford to do

Rocks themselves aren't a strategy but an enabler. If you remove access to 'cheap mana' (by cost not price) then folks have to focus their game on answering the more explosive green decks since they can still do the big plays. I also think - where do you draw the link on the fast mana rocks? Just Mana Crypt/Sol Ring/Vault? All legal Moxen?
and they can only use the more efficient 'answers' or  threats
which just shifts the cost
Show me on the doll where the green ramp player touched you Henry
on my Mox Taint
I just think you're overestimating the power of green ramp
Decks don't get more green than Reki, and it's entirely reliant on creatures for everything, and there's only so much ramp I want
Sure, but thats a specific 'theme' deck that doesn't really represent the majority of green decks.
I just don't think green ramp is that busted. You have to give up a card for every extra ramp spell you run.
If you're running 5 more ramp spells than a non-green player then that is 5 less draw spells, removal spells, etc. I just think it mostly washes
It isn't busted, but it is desirable. I guess my other point is removing access to fast rocks forces people to likely build more decks with green in them to get access to ramp.
I just don't think it's that desireable. Given a choice between running 15 draw and 5 ramp or 5 ramp and 15 draw I'll go 15 draw every time.

But we're talking about the whole vs. the specific. That isn't how most folks like to build decks. They want to do big splashy things vs. eat their veggies. That's part of EDH's appeal to a lot of folks.
Also, in mono-white, where do I get 15 draw spells?

Or Thrassios with a sink, OG Omanath, etc
But again, the specific vs. the aggregate.
